description:
&lt;p&gt;Nurses looking for an exciting challenge and a wealth of opportunities are encouraged to join our current nursing workforce who continually go above and beyond to ensure the Trust delivers outstanding patient care. We have opportunities for both highly motivated newly qualified and experienced nurses.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;M2 is a 27 bedded ward, specialising in acute general medicine. The ward has patients with a variety of clinical presentations and conditions, ranging from respiratory, gastrointestinal, cardiology and diabetes and endocrine conditions, with patients usually being admitted directly from our Emergency Assessment Unit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The nursing staff on M2 have achieved a Green status in the Nursing Assessment and Accreditation system and are working towards SCAPE (Safe, Clean and Personal every time) status.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be supported within a strong management structure, providing excellence in care, and encouragement to maximise your potential, development and success. We welcome both newly qualified nurses and experienced nurses wanting to develop their knowledge and skills in Diabetes care. You will be supported by the senior nurses on M2 and have a supernumery period to enable you to orientate yourself to the ward before caring for your caseload of patients. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;In return we can offer you:-&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;If you are a newly qualified nurse we will pay your first year&#39;s NMC registration fee as well as paying you at Band 4 until you receive you NMC PIN&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Competitive relocation package (subject to conditions)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Full induction programme supported by our dedicated Practice Development Team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Specialised ongoing educational development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support from senior nursing team and highly specialised nurse&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will also have access to the following staff benefits:&lt;br /&gt;• Car Lease Scheme&lt;br /&gt;• Gymflex Scheme&lt;br /&gt;• Discounted First Bus Tickets&lt;br /&gt;• Mobile Phones – Salary Sacrifice&lt;br /&gt;• Cycle to Work Scheme&lt;br /&gt;• Nursery on Site / Child Care Vouchers&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In line with the Trust’s Single Equality Scheme we welcome applications from everyone irrespective of ethnic origin, disability, age, gender, sexual preference, disability, nationality, religion, marital status, social back ground or trade union membership&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name  Angelique Woodl stencroft&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title Ward Manager&lt;/p&gt;
